*****
[2] Diarrhea, displaced persons - Cambodia (Kandal province)
Date: Wed 1 Feb 2012
Source: The Phnom Penh Post [edited]
http://www.phnompenhpost.com/index.php/2012020154258/National-news/skin-conditions-diarrhoea-hit-b-keila-evictees.html


Hundreds of evicted Borei Keila [a large poor urban community in Phnom Penh] residents living at a relocation site in Kandal province are suffering from diarrhea, as well as skin ailments and fever after consecutive days of rain, an NGO doctor said yesterday [31 Jan 2012].

Dr Nhean Sarin, a medical officer with rights group Licadho, told the Post yesterday [31 Jan 2012] that Borei Keila residents relocated to Ponhear Leu district's Srah Po village in early January [2012] were also at more risk of catching malaria and cholera.

"The raining over a few consecutive days caused them to develop fever, chills, and diarrhea due to them having inadequate sleep because their plastic, no-wall tents cannot stand the rain," he said, adding that many were also suffering from a shortage of food.

[Byline: Khouth Sophakchakrya]

