[3] Cholera - Congo DR
Date:Sat 28 Jan 2012
Source: Agence France-Presse (AFP) [edited]
http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5j1dxPcHozp0HcqVj7Ik9MqAxJpkw?docId=CNG.871f4204301feda9723a1cb343f5afe3.101


Cholera cases have soared in the Democratic Republic of Congo in recent weeks, the UN said on Friday, 27 Jan 2012, bringing the number of people infected in the year-long outbreak to 22 000 with 584 deaths. Aid agencies have been trying to halt the spread of the water-borne disease that has ravaged 8 of the country's 11 provinces since January 2011.

"There has been a spike in cases" since mid-December 2011, with figures on the rise in the capital Kinshasa in particular, the UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (OCHA) said. Cholera, a contagious intestinal infection, has taken its heaviest toll on eastern regions however, with a quarter of all cases reported in Sud-Kivu province.

