*****
[4] Diarrhea - El Salvador, Honduras
Date: Wed 1 Feb 2012
Source: El Nacional [machine transl., edited]
http://www.el-nacional.com/noticia/20678/22/El-Salvador-reporta-siete-muertos-por-diarrea-comun-a-nivel-nacional.html


The deputy minister of Salvadoran Health, Violeta Menjivar, stated to journalists that during January 2012 common diarrhea caused "nationwide, 7 deaths," without further details. In the same period were recorded in the El Salvador 46 761 cases of diarrhea, some 19 178 more than the 27 583 recorded in January 2011, according to official information.

The Honduran health authorities declared an alert on the borders with El Salvador and Nicaragua by what they described as an outbreak of rotavirus in both countries, without offering details.

